servings: 2
time required: 20 minutes
---

Fill and boil your #kettle{}. Trim the @pak choi{1}, then separate the leaves.

Halve any thick @Tenderstem® broccoli{80%g} stems lengthways, then cut into thirds.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} on medium heat with @salt{1/4%tsp}.

Add the @egg noodle nests{2}, broccoli and pak choi to the water. Cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop the noodles sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and fry until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. It's cooked when
> no longer pink in the middle.

Add the @Thai style spice blend{1%portion} (add less if you'd prefer things milder)
and garlic to the beef. Stir-fry for ~{30%seconds}.

Pour in the @hoisin sauce{64%g}, @teriyaki sauce{50%g}, @soy sauce{15%g} and @water{100%ml}
and bring to a boil. Reduce the heat slightly, then simmer until the sauce has thickened,
~{2-3%minutes}.

Once the sauce has thickened, toss the noodles and pak choi into the beef mixture.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} if needed.

Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick.

Share your quick beef noodles between your bowls.

Enjoy!